        "subject": "LU-17852 gss: improve kernel key usage",
        "message": "LU-17852 gss: improve kernel key usage\n\nOnce kernel key has been instantiated, set proper flags so that\nin-kernel processes can dispose of the key without restrictions in\ncase of error:\n- KEY_FLAG_ROOT_CAN_CLEAR: set if key can be cleared by root without\n  permission\n- KEY_FLAG_ROOT_CAN_INVAL: set if key can be invalidated by root\n  without permission\nAlso explictly mark the key as expired from userspace in case of\nerror.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: testgroup=review-dne-selinux-ssk-part-2\nTest-Parameters: kerberos=true testlist=sanity-krb5\nSigned-off-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I5f1ea2d265e358454a23bee3880b6e024b507659\n"
      },
